and

00:12:36.280 --> 00:12:37.280
&gt;&gt;help them,

00:12:37.280 --> 00:12:41.940
Larry: yeah, to count the ballots.

00:12:41.940 --> 00:12:43.340
[ LAUGHTER ]

00:12:43.340 --> 00:12:44.740
[ INAUDIBLE ]

00:12:44.740 --> 00:12:55.360
Larry: Oh sorry, I was going to transition
to that, sorry. I think that I think elections

00:12:55.360 --> 00:12:59.970
are an area we can learn from because there's
been so much work done by a lot of great people

00:12:59.970 --> 00:13:03.280
that there are actually procedures in place
now that we know if we have the following

00:13:03.280 --> 00:13:07.420
10 things, than we have an election that's
probably mostly fair or we know whether we

00:13:07.420 --> 00:13:13.050
did or not. And I think we need those set
of 10 things for other parts of the government.

00:13:13.050 --> 00:13:17.070
So you know there's great organizations that
are trying to do things like just measure

00:13:17.070 --> 00:13:20.800
you know if you're putting money into a school
does it actually get built? You know, can

00:13:20.800 --> 00:13:27.110
you see the school, does it walls, does it
have books and those kind of things. How do

00:13:27.110 --> 00:13:30.821
you measure that, that scale? And so what
are the 10 things that you need to do to make

00:13:30.821 --> 00:13:33.410
sure that when you gave the money for the
school that they really appear and they have

00:13:33.410 --> 00:13:38.700
teachers and students and all those things.
And I think if we got some of those procedures

00:13:38.700 --> 00:13:43.600
and the rules right for these governments
and we got the accountability and the understanding

00:13:43.600 --> 00:13:47.860
of what's going on I think we'll make a lot
of progress in, around the corruption side

00:13:47.860 --> 00:13:52.300
and so on. My brother really likes, he has
a phrase ISO 9000 for governments. You know

00:13:52.300 --> 00:13:58.610
if you go around in these developing countries
you see a factory. They alway have an ISO

00:13:58.610 --> 00:14:03.590
9000 banner, which is basically you know this
burocratic stuff about how you make sure the

00:14:03.590 --> 00:14:08.090
stuff you make is really what you claim it
is and it's safe the and the bolts don't break

00:14:08.090 --> 00:14:11.730
if you build a building out of the nails they
don't, you know your building doesn't fall

00:14:11.730 --> 00:14:15.720
down. And we don't have the equivalent for
governments, if we did, maybe that would help

00:14:15.720 --> 00:14:20.650
a lot. And I think we're talking about that
and Larry alluded to it.

00:14:20.650 --> 00:14:25.050
&gt;&gt;This organization that Larry's talking about
Parthown, we've given them some money and

00:14:25.050 --> 00:14:31.330
they're actually doing surveys of not the
input or the output but the throughput of

00:14:31.330 --> 00:14:35.650
education to see whether kids are actually
literate, not whether the government says

00:14:35.650 --> 00:14:39.790
they are or whether the school teachers say
they are, because parents who are not literate

00:14:39.790 --> 00:14:45.540
can't gauge the literacy and the education
that the kids are getting. So there's really

00:14:45.540 --> 00:14:49.890
three parts to this. First, I want to say
a nice thing about the government of India,

00:14:49.890 --> 00:14:55.540
you know they've got three one hundred billion
dollar programs to address issues of intractable

00:14:55.540 --> 00:15:01.240
extreme poverty. And one of them a program
called the Right to Information Act. You know

00:15:01.240 --> 00:15:05.730
we have one of those in the United States?
But this one has teeth in it. If you don't

00:15:05.730 --> 00:15:12.520
get your grain allotment that you are entitled
to, you go to any magistrate and you say,

00:15:12.520 --> 00:15:16.590
I didn't get my grain allotment. They have
30 days to tell you who touched that grain

00:15:16.590 --> 00:15:21.250
allotment at every single weigh-in in the
chain and if any one of those guys doesn't

00:15:21.250 --> 00:15:25.830
tell you what they did with it, they go to
jail. And they actually make people go to

00:15:25.830 --> 00:15:31.990
jail. It's an amazing piece of legislation.
Likewise, they have a Right to Work Act, where

00:15:31.990 --> 00:15:38.890
the government is allocated 100 billion dollars
for people in India who, you know, on average

00:15:38.890 --> 00:15:44.940
can 300 million people earn less than a dollar
a day? So they have offered anyone a dollar

00:15:44.940 --> 00:15:50.860
a day of work for two hundred days. Two hundred
dollars a year. But the problem is corruption.

00:15:50.860 --> 00:15:54.940
The problem is it's the leakiest pipe in the
world when you start off with 100 billion

00:15:54.940 --> 00:15:59.550
dollars in Dali and you've got to get it to
any other place in India. So they've built

00:15:59.550 --> 00:16:04.940
the best program evaluation system I've ever
seen. It's called the social audit. Forget

00:16:04.940 --> 00:16:08.670
about where the money started or how it gets
there at the end of the day they bring all

00:16:08.670 --> 00:16:14.191
of the landless peasants together who are
entitled to get this work and get paid and

00:16:14.191 --> 00:16:18.960
they pull out the roster. And they check the
thumb prints on the roster in front of 2,000

00:16:18.960 --> 00:16:23.490
village. I attended some of these myself where
corrupt individuals were just put in jail

00:16:23.490 --> 00:16:28.130
immediately in front of everybody and thousands
of people cheered because they've never felt

00:16:28.130 --> 00:16:34.190
so empowered. I think these are some of the
things that we need to be looking at. There

00:16:34.190 --> 00:16:39.030
are lots of solutions out there. The other
part of it is that I don't think that people

00:16:39.030 --> 00:16:42.760
in Ganna know what the people in India are
doing. I don't think there's much of what

00:16:42.760 --> 00:16:48.970
the UA used to call TCDC, Technical Cooperation
Amongst Developing Countries. We with our

00:16:48.970 --> 00:16:54.410
technology and others should be able to spot
those things which work in one place and share

00:16:54.410 --> 00:16:59.310
it with everybody. You can be very optimistic
if you go to a social audit in India, I'll

00:16:59.310 --> 00:17:00.310
tell you.

